		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I did a little digging on Alibaba and found one company, Cheertone Technology, seems to be the only one left that sells an 8-bit game system with a keyboard.  They don't list it on their own website.<br /><br />I'd be surprised if there was any useful software that came with it, other than bootleg games though.  I doubt there's even a way to save data (though a FlashROM-based cart should be able to do it).  Might be worth asking them for details, but prepare to be disappointed.  Supposedly $6 each, but 1000 pieces minimum order...  There seems to be nothing like it on Aliexpress, where it's normal to have smaller orders.<br /><br />CT-K802 <a href="https://www.alibaba.com/product-detail/8-bit-electronic-keyboard-Game-player_245494509.html?spm=a2700.7724838.2017115.400.3c93b095chRLy9" class="postlink">https://www.alibaba.com/product-detail/8-bit-electronic-keyboard-Game-player_245494509.html?spm=a2700.7724838.2017115.400.3c93b095chRLy9</a><br />CT-K803 <a href="https://www.alibaba.com/product-detail/8-Bit-Keyboard-Game-Player-CT_237010565.html?spm=a2700.7724838.2017115.101.3c93b095chRLy9" class="postlink">https://www.alibaba.com/product-detail/8-Bit-Keyboard-Game-Player-CT_237010565.html?spm=a2700.7724838.2017115.101.3c93b095chRLy9</a><br />CT-K803 (again) <a href="https://www.alibaba.com/product-detail/Cheap-Price-Children-8-bit-Handheld_60679033969.html?spm=a2700.7724838.2017115.243.3c93b095chRLy9" class="postlink">https://www.alibaba.com/product-detail/Cheap-Price-Children-8-bit-Handheld_60679033969.html?spm=a2700.7724838.2017115.243.3c93b095chRLy9</a>

		

