		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The Famicom keyboard can be plugged into a NES with an adapter like ENIO. But a Famicom is cheaper than a NES anyway, so I'd just get a Famicom (although depending on where you live it may or may not be harder to get hold of).<br /><br />I translated most of both Family BASIC manuals to English, links are in <a href="http://www.famicomworld.com/forum/index.php?topic=11959.0" class="postlink">this thread</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
